          "content": "Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here's a comprehensive read-through:\n\n---\n\n## NXP — NEXUS Protocol: Codebase Overview\n\n### What it is\n\nA custom transport protocol over UDP, heavily inspired by QUIC (RFC 9000). Written in C23, with a Go bindings layer. The core design principle is **Sans-I/O**: the protocol engine never touches sockets — it only consumes/produces raw bytes. The caller handles all I/O.\n\n---\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\ninclude/nxp/       — Public API headers\nsrc/\n  api/             — Public API bridge (nxp_api.c, config.c, error.c)\n  core/            — Protocol engine (connection, streams, frames, packets, handshake, ACK, migration, etc.)\n  crypto/          — AEAD, HKDF, X25519, header protection, session tickets, retry tokens, PoW\n  congestion/      — BBR v1 congestion control, delivery rate, pacing, windowed filter\n  memory/          — Arena, pool, slab allocators\n  platform/        — Event loop (epoll/kqueue/IOCP), sockets, threads, time\n  transport/       — Pluggable transport backends (UDP, WebSocket, TCP)\n  util/            — Hash map, ring buffer, priority queue, varint, CRC32c, logging, metrics, flight recorder\n  logging/         — Optional Quill-based C++ logging\ntests/             — Unit, integration, fuzz, Go tests\nbindings/go/       — CGo Go package\nbenches/           — TCP/UDP/WebSocket benchmarks\nexamples/          — Usage examples\ncmake/             — Build helpers\n```\n\n---\n\n### Public API (`include/nxp/`)\n\nFive headers, one umbrella:\n\n- **`nxp_types.h`** — All enums and structs: `nxp_conn_id`, `nxp_addr`, stream/connection/crypto/packet/frame types, `nxp_conn_stats`, opaque handles, callback typedefs.\n- **`nxp_error.h`** — `nxp_result` (code + optional file/line in debug), 20 error codes, `NXP_SUCCESS`/`NXP_ERROR()` macros.\n- **`nxp_config.h`** — `nxp_config*` builder: cert/key files, ALPN, stream limits, idle timeout, heartbeat interval.\n- **`nxp_connection.h`** — `nxp_connect()`, `nxp_conn_close()`, state/stats getters, callbacks.\n- **`nxp_stream.h`** — `nxp_stream_open()`, `nxp_stream_send/recv()`, shutdown, state/backpressure queries.\n- **`nxp_listener.h`** — `nxp_listen()` (UDP), `nxp_listen_url()` (scheme-based), `nxp_listener_close()`.\n- **`nxp.h`** — Umbrella: `nxp_init()`, `nxp_shutdown()`, `nxp_run()`/`nxp_poll()`, `nxp_connect_url()` (scheme-based), metrics API.\n\nSupported URL schemes: `nxp://` (UDP native), `ws://`, `wss://`, `ntc://` (raw TCP), `nrtc://` (WebRTC, future).\n\n---\n\n### Core Engine (`src/core/`)\n\n**`connection_internal.h`** — The central internal header. Defines:\n- `nxp_conn` struct: CIDs, state, packet numbering, ACK state, crypto state (app + 0-RTT), migration, congestion control (BBR vtable + pacer + delivery rate), heartbeat, streams hash map, flow control, scheduler, config, stats.\n- `nxp_stream_s` struct: send/recv ring buffers with offset tracking, per-stream flow control, per-stream rate limiter, backpressure callback, scheduler linkage.\n- Full internal API: `nxp_conn_create/destroy`, `nxp_conn_recv/send` (the Sans-I/O entry points), `nxp_conn_open_stream`, `nxp_conn_stream_send/recv`, timeout management, heartbeat, auto-reconnect, per-stream rate limiting.\n\n**`connection.c`** (~53KB) — The main protocol engine. Handles packet receive/send, frame dispatch, stream scheduling, ACK/loss callbacks, CC integration, state machine transitions (validated via `is_valid_conn_state_transition`).\n\n**`frame.c`** / **`frame_internal.h`** — Encode/decode for all 25+ frame types. STREAM frames use QUIC-style OFF/LEN/FIN bit encoding (0x08–0x0F). Tagged union `nxp_frame` for parsed frames.\n\n**`packet.c`** / **`packet_internal.h`** — Long header (Initial/Handshake/Retry/0-RTT) and short header (1-RTT) wire format. Packet number truncation/reconstruction. Header bit masks documented inline.\n\n**`handshake.c`** / **`handshake_internal.h`** — 1-RTT handshake state machine. Flow: `ClientHello` (Initial, X25519 pubkey) → `ServerHello` (Handshake, X25519 pubkey + AEAD selection) → `HANDSHAKE_DONE` (1-RTT). Transcript hashing for key derivation. Phase 6: 0-RTT resumption via session tickets.\n\n**`ack.c`** — ACK/loss detection. Tracks sent packets (up to 1024), received PN ranges (up to 64), RTT estimation (smoothed + variance + min), RACK-style time-based loss detection, PTO (Probe Timeout), delayed ACK timer (25ms).\n\n**`stream.c`** — Stream send/recv buffer management. Offset-based byte stream with retransmission support (`on_loss` rewinds `sent_offset`).\n\n**`flow_control.c`** — Connection-level and per-stream flow control. Tracks `peer_max_data` / `local_max_data`, auto-sends `MAX_DATA` updates when window is half consumed.\n\n**`scheduler.c`** — Round-robin stream scheduler using a circular doubly-linked list. `nxp_sched_next()` picks the next stream with unsent data.\n\n**`migration.c`** / **`migration_internal.h`** — Connection migration: PATH_CHALLENGE/RESPONSE path validation, CID pool management (up to 8 peer CIDs), NEW_CONNECTION_ID / RETIRE_CONNECTION_ID frame handling. CID routing support (node ID prefix for load balancers).\n\n**`listener.c`** / **`listener_internal.h`** — Multi-connection server. CID → `nxp_conn*` hash map routing. Stateless Retry support. Round-robin send loop. Per-IP rate limiting (100 pps/IP, 1s window). Up to 4096 concurrent connections by default.\n\n**`heartbeat.c`** — HEARTBEAT frame (0x20) keep-alive. Configurable interval, 3-miss dead detection, RTT measurement via echo timestamps.\n\n**`session_export.c`** — Serialize/deserialize connection state for server-to-server migration. Exports CIDs, crypto keys, flow control, RTT estimates. Wire format is little-endian with magic `\"NXPS\"`.\n\n**`rate_limit.h`** — Per-IP DoS rate limiter (header-only, token bucket via hash map).\n\n**`stream_rate.h`** — Per-stream token-bucket rate limiter (header-only). 100ms burst, configurable bytes/sec.\n\n**`heartbeat_internal.h`**, **`validation.h`** — Heartbeat state, input validation limits (1MB max frame data, 64K streams, 1 exabyte max offset).\n\n---\n\n### Crypto (`src/crypto/`)\n\nAll backed by OpenSSL 3.x.\n\n- **`aead.c`** — AES-256-GCM and ChaCha20-Poly1305 encrypt/decrypt via EVP API.\n- **`hkdf.c`** — HKDF-Extract, HKDF-Expand, HKDF-Expand-Label (NXP label format: `\"nxp1 \" + label`).\n- **`handshake_crypto.c`** — X25519 keygen + shared secret, initial key derivation from DCID (using `NXP_INITIAL_SALT`), traffic key derivation from secrets.\n- **`header_protection.c`** — AES-ECB (for AES-GCM) or ChaCha20 (for ChaCha20-Poly1305) header masking/unmasking of first byte + packet number bytes.\n- **`session_ticket.c`** — AES-256-GCM encrypted session tickets for 0-RTT. Includes expiry, resumption secret, AEAD algo, transport params. Strike register for replay protection.\n- **`retry_token.c`** — Stateless retry tokens: AES-256-GCM encrypted, binds client IP + original DCID + timestamp.\n- **`proof_of_work.c`** — SHA-256 PoW challenge/solve/verify. Difficulty 8–32 leading zero bits. For handshake DoS mitigation.\n- **`secure_mem.h`** — `nxp_secure_zero()` (wraps `explicit_bzero`/`SecureZeroMemory`), constant-time `nxp_secure_compare()`.\n\n---\n\n### Congestion Control (`src/congestion/`)\n\n- **`bbr.c`** / **`bbr_internal.h`** — BBR v1 state machine: STARTUP → DRAIN → PROBE_BW ↔ PROBE_RTT. Integer-ratio gain factors. Windowed max BW filter (10 rounds), windowed min RTT (10s). Pipe-filling detection (3 rounds without 25% growth).\n- **`delivery_rate.c`** — Per-packet bandwidth sampling. Snapshots `delivered` + timestamps on send; computes `delivery_rate = delta_delivered / delta_time` on ACK.\n- **`pacing.c`** — Token-bucket pacer. BBR sets rate; pacer enforces it. Max burst: 10 packets.\n- **`windowed_filter.h`** — Header-only Kathleen Nichols windowed min/max filter (3-sample sliding window).\n- **`cc_interface.h`** — Vtable (`nxp_cc_ops`) for pluggable CC: `on_sent`, `on_ack`, `on_loss`, `get_cwnd`, `get_pacing_rate`, `in_slow_start`, `get_send_quantum`.\n\n---\n\n### Transport Layer (`src/transport/`, `src/platform/transport.h`)\n\nPluggable backends registered at init time via `nxp_transport_register()`.\n\n- **`transport.h`** — `nxp_transport` (client) and `nxp_transport_listener` (server) vtables. Factory: `nxp_transport_connect(url)` / `nxp_transport_listen(url, ...)`.\n- **`udp/transport_udp.c`** — UDP backend (POSIX sockets).\n- **`websocket/transport_ws.c`** — WebSocket backend. Uses `ws_handshake.c` (RFC 6455 HTTP Upgrade) and `ws_frame.c` (RFC 6455 framing). NXP packets are carried as binary WebSocket frames.\n- **`tcp/transport_tcp.c`** — Raw TCP backend with 2-byte length prefix framing.\n\n---\n\n### Platform (`src/platform/`)\n\n- **`event_loop.h`** / **`event_loop.c`** — Backend-agnostic event loop. Shared timer management (min-heap priority queue). Backend vtable: `add_socket`, `mod_socket`, `del_socket`, `poll`, `wakeup`.\n- **`linux/epoll_event_loop.c`** — epoll + eventfd backend.\n- **`darwin/kqueue_event_loop.c`** — kqueue + pipe backend.\n- **`windows/iocp_event_loop.c`** — IOCP stub (in development).\n- **`linux/posix_socket.c`**, **`linux/posix_time.c`**, **`linux/posix_thread.c`** — POSIX socket/time/thread wrappers.\n- **`windows/winsock_socket.c`**, **`windows/win_time.c`**, **`windows/win_thread.c`** — Windows equivalents.\n- **`platform_atomic.h`**, **`platform_endian.h`**, **`platform_memory.h`** — Portability headers.\n\n---\n\n### Memory (`src/memory/`)\n\n- **`arena.c`** — Bump allocator with linked 64KB blocks. `nxp_arena_new(arena, T)` macro. Reset without free for reuse.\n- **`pool.c`** — Fixed-size object pool. O(1) alloc/free via intrusive free list.\n- **`slab.c`** — Slab allocator (multiple pools for different sizes).\n- **`packet_buffer.c`** — Pre-allocated packet buffer pool.\n\n---\n\n### Utilities (`src/util/`)\n\n- **`hash_map.c`** — Robin Hood open-addressing hash map. `uint64_t` keys (CID hash, stream ID). `nxp_hash_map_foreach()` for iteration.\n- **`priority_queue.c`** — Min-heap for timer management.\n- **`ring_buffer.c`** — Lock-free SPSC byte ring buffer (atomic read/write positions).\n- **`varint.c`** — QUIC RFC 9000 varint encoding (2-bit prefix, 1/2/4/8 bytes, max 2^62−1).\n- **`crc32c.c`** — CRC32c checksum.\n- **`flight_recorder.c`** — Circular 1000-entry event log (packet RX/TX, crypto ops, state changes, errors, ACK/loss). Useful for post-mortem debugging.\n- **`error_tracker.c`** — Error frequency tracking.\n- **`log.c`** / **`log.h`** — Compile-time filtered logging (TRACE/DEBUG/INFO/WARN/ERROR/FATAL). User-installable callback. C23 `__VA_OPT__` for zero-arg macros.\n- **`metrics.c`** — Prometheus text format metrics export.\n- **`checked_int.h`** — Overflow-safe arithmetic wrapping C23 `<stdckdint.h>` with manual fallback.\n- **`intrusive_list.h`** — Intrusive doubly-linked list.\n\n---\n\n### Public API Bridge (`src/api/`)\n\n**`nxp_api.c`** — The glue layer. Maintains a global singleton `g_nxp` with the event loop, linked lists of all `nxp_api_conn` and `nxp_listener` wrappers. Each `nxp_api_conn` holds the internal `nxp_conn*`, a `nxp_transport*`, and an event loop timer. On socket readability: calls `nxp_conn_recv()` → `nxp_api_flush_conn()` (drains `nxp_conn_send()` to the transport). On timer: calls `nxp_conn_on_timeout()` → flush → rearm. `nxp_run()` / `nxp_poll()` drive the event loop.\n\n---\n\n### Build System\n\nCMake 3.25+, C23 required. Internal static libs: `nxp_util` → `nxp_memory` → `nxp_platform` → `nxp_congestion`, `nxp_crypto`, `nxp_core` → `nxp_api` → `nxp` (shared) / `nxp_static`. OpenSSL 3.0+ required. Optional: io_uring, ASAN/UBSAN/TSAN, fuzzing, Quill logging.\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Sans-I/O**: `nxp_conn_recv/send` are pure byte-in/byte-out. No syscalls inside the engine. Makes testing trivial and transport-agnostic.\n2. **QUIC-inspired wire format**: varint encoding, long/short headers, packet number spaces, AEAD + header protection — all structurally identical to QUIC RFC 9000.\n3. **Pluggable CC via vtable**: BBR is the default but the interface supports Cubic or others.\n4. **Pluggable transport via vtable**: same NXP protocol engine runs over UDP, WebSocket, or TCP framing.\n5. **C23**: uses `[[nodiscard]]`, `nullptr`, `_BitInt`, `<stdckdint.h>`, `__VA_OPT__`, `alignas`.\n6. **Security layers**: AEAD encryption, header protection, retry tokens (address validation), session tickets (0-RTT), PoW challenges (DoS), per-IP rate limiting, constant-time comparisons, `explicit_bzero` for key material."
